This paper focuses on target-guided open-domain conversation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel dynamic knowledge routing network and a dual discourse-level target-guided strategy, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the retrieval of relevant responses, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and the use of knowledge relations between candidate keywords, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
